Timberwolves 94, Trail Blazers 87
</SUBHEAD>
<P>
   MINNEAPOLIS (AP) -- Terrell Brandon scored 28 points and shut down Damon
Stoudamire as the Minnesota Timberwolves staved off elimination with a 94-87
victory over the Portland Trail Blazers on Sunday. Kevin Garnett, who has just
two triple-doubles in five NBA seasons, had his second triple-double in a week
with 23 points, 12 rebounds and 10 assists as the Wolves pulled to 2-1 in the
best-of-five series. Game 4 is Tuesday night at Target Center.
</P>
