<HEADLINE> Report: 5 Die in Train Collision  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   JAKARTA, Indonesia (AP) -- A head-on collision between two
passenger trains southwest of the capital, Jakarta, killed at least
five people, news reports said Monday.
</P>
<P>
   The collision between a Jakarta-bound train and a train going
from Jakarta to the West Java town of Merak occurred at the village
of Mekar Sari, 20 miles southwest of Jakarta, said the private SCTV
station.
</P>
<P>
   Lt. Col. Pudji Hartanto, chief of the local police, who was
interviewed by the station, said four people were killed instantly
and more than 20 others were injured.
</P>
<P>
   Meanwhile, Sonora, a private radio station, reported that at
least one person died on way to the hospital.
</P>
