<HEADLINE> AP Names Correspondent in Austin  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   AUSTIN, Texas (AP) -- Kelley Shannon, correspondent for The
Associated Press in San Antonio, has been promoted to correspondent
in charge of the AP's Austin bureau.
</P>
<P>
   The appointment was announced Monday by Texas Chief of Bureau
John Lumpkin. She succeeds Mike Holmes, who has been promoted to
chief of bureau in Omaha, Neb.
</P>
<P>
   Shannon joined the AP in Dallas in 1988 and became San Antonio
correspondent the following year. She previously was a reporter for
the Savannah (Ga.) News-Press and the Palestine (Texas)
Herald-Press.
</P>
<P>
   Shannon, 37, is a graduate of the University of Texas.
