<HEADLINE> Liza Minnelli Cancels Tour Dates  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Liza Minnelli is in the hospital with a hip
problem and has canceled upcoming tour dates for ''Minnelli on
Minnelli.''
</P>
<P>
   ''My show is physically demanding and I was doing more damage
with each performance and causing myself a great deal of pain. I
simply could not continue with the show,'' she said in a statement
Monday.
</P>
<P>
   ''It became clear that it wasn't possible to give my fans, who
have gotten me through this before, the show that I love to do and
that they deserve,'' she said.
</P>
<P>
   Minnelli, 54, has had two surgeries on her right hip. The
replacements have hampered her mobility and several of the show's
numbers are done sitting in a chair.
</P>
<P>
   The current ailment, described as an ''acute and severe hip
condition,'' involves her left hip, the statement said.
</P>
