<HEADLINE> AP Financial News at 5:10 p.m. EDT  </HEADLINE>
Monday, May 1, 2000
<TEXT>
<P>
   Dow Ends Up 77; Nasdaq Up 97
</P>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Investors brushed off worries about Microsoft's
future today, sending its shares higher and fueling a rally in
technology stocks that spread to the broad market. The Dow Jones
industrial average rose 77.87 to close at 10,811.78. The Nasdaq
composite index rose 97.83 to 3,958.49. Broader stock indicators
were also higher. The proposal by the Justice Department and 17
states to split Microsoft into two companies was widely expected,
and many investors determined that the possibility of a breakup had
already taken its toll on Microsoft stock. It was at 73 7/16, up 3
11/16. Before today's session, Microsoft's share price had declined
by about 40 percent since the start of the year. Technology
companies that compete with Microsoft were mostly higher. Red Hat
and VA Linux, which sell the Linux operating system, both rose.
</P>
<P>
   Financial Figures
</P>
<P>
   New York (AP) -- Financial figures at the close
Dow Industrials:        10,811.78  + 77.87
