<HEADLINE> Kids Get Ill From Mock Space Shuttle  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   WAUSAU, Wis. (AP) -- A school bus designed to look like the space
shuttle malfunctioned Monday, spewing carbon dioxide fumes into the
vehicle and sickening more than two dozen fifth-graders.
</P>
<P>
   Science classes use the space shuttle -- a bus painted black and
white and nicknamed Apollo Condor -- to study spaceflight.
</P>
<P>
   Wausau Schools Superintendent Charles Skurka said the students
became dizzy, nauseated and short of breath. ''There was one young
lady that I ran to initially, she was actually vomiting,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
   Wausau Hospital treated 29 students and a bus driver. All were
released.
</P>
<P>
   A coupling came loose on a line that feeds carbon dioxide to
exhaust cones on the back of the bus. The carbon dioxide shot into
the bus.
</P>
</TEXT>
