<HEADLINE> AP Corrects Bank of America Story  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SAN FRANCISCO (AP) -- The Associated Press on April 1 reported
erroneously that Bank of America closed its ATMs to non-customers
in San Francisco.
</P>
<P>
   Both Wells Fargo and Bank of America closed their ATMs last
November to non-customers in Santa Monica, where the city council
banned charging extra ATM fees to non-customers.
</P>
<P>
   Bank of America had threatened to take the same step in San
Francisco if city's voter-approved ban were implemented. However, a
federal judge blocked the San Francisco ordinance and the bank has
continued to allow non-customers to use its ATMs.
</P>
