<HEADLINE> Dutch Numico To Buy Rexall Sundown  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   AMSTERDAM, Netherlands (AP) -- The Dutch specialty foods company
Royal Numico NV is buying Rexall Sundown Inc., a U.S.-based maker
of nutritional supplements and consumer health products, for about
$1.7 billion.
</P>
<P>
   News of the deal disclosed Monday drove Rexall Sundown's shares
up by 21 percent in midday New York trading.
</P>
<P>
   Rexall, based in Boca Raton, Fla. will give Numico a strong
position in the fast-growing American food supplements market, the
Dutch group said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
   The two companies will have combined annual sales of more than
$4.5 billion. Numico expects the merger will enable it to save
$22.8 million annually.
</P>
<P>
   Numico plans to finance the deal -- already approved by Rexall's
management -- by issuing new shares and bonds and by refinancing
existing loans, according to a company statement.
</P>
<P>
   Numico is offering $24 per share in cash for Rexall Sundown's
shares. It will also assume $114 million in debt, boosting the
total value of the deal to $1.8 billion.
</P>
<P>
   Rexall Sundown shares rose $4.18}, or nearly 22 percent, to
$23.43} a share in trading at 4 p.m. on the Nasdaq Stock Market.
</P>
<P>
   The purchase is expected to be completed within two months.
</P>
<P>
   Last year, Numico took over General Nutrition Companies Inc.,
which made up 50 percent of the group's profit growth in 1999.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
