<HEADLINE> Abortion Activist To Take Leave  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON (AP) -- Kate Michelman, president of the National
Abortion and Reproductive Rights Action League, said Monday she is
taking a three-month leave for health reasons,
</P>
<P>
   ''On advice from my doctors, I will be taking a three-month
medical leave of absence beginning the first week of May,''
Michelman, 57, said in a brief statement that contained no
specifics of her condition. ''This leave is necessary to
concentrate on an intensive program of physical therapy.''
</P>
<P>
   Michelman said she will return in August ''to continue
campaigning vigorously to elect'' a president and Senate and House
members who support a woman's right to an abortion.
</P>
<P>
   She has been president of the abortion rights lobby for 16
years.
</P>
<P>
   In February, the organization broke its tradition of not backing
a presidential candidate during the primaries by announcing its
endorsement of Democrat Al Gore over rival Bill Bradley.
</P>
</TEXT>
