<DATE_TIME> 2000-05-01 23:12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Padres Make Bullpen Change  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SAN DIEGO (AP) -- The San Diego Padres started retooling their
porous bullpen on Monday by optioning right-hander Will Cunnane to
Triple-A Las Vegas and recalling right-hander Buddy Carlyle.
</P>
<P>
   Cunnane was 1-0 with a 4.09 ERA in 12 appearances. He struck out
16 but walked nine in 11 innings, allowing five earned runs and
seven hits.
</P>
<P>
   On Saturday night against Atlanta, he replaced rookie starter
Rodrigo Lopez with a 4-1 lead and put two runners on before Carlos
Almanzar came on and allowed Andres Galarraga's three-run homer.
The Braves went on to win 7-4 in 12 innings. Almanzar gave up a
three-run homer in all three weekend losses to the Braves.
</P>
<P>
   Carlyle was 0-1 with a 6.45 ERA in four starts at Las Vegas.
Last year, he went 1-3 with a 5.97 ERA in seven late-season starts
for the Padres in his first big league stint.
</P>
<P>
   Meanwhile, reliever Rodney Myers could be activated from the
15-day disabled list on Friday if his rehab assignment at Class A
Rancho Cucamonga goes well. He allowed one hit in one scoreless
inning Sunday and is scheduled to pitch again Tuesday and
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   Myers, acquired in an offseason trade with the Chicago Cubs, has
been on the DL since March 29 with a partially torn right rotator
cuff that eventually will require surgery.
</P>
</TEXT>
