<DATE_TIME> 2000-05-01 23:14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Minnesota Wild Join NHL  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   ST. PAUL (AP) -- The Minnesota Wild has received full NHL
franchise status.
</P>
<P>
   ''This is a defining moment in the history of the Minnesota
Wild,'' chief executive officer Jac Sperling said Monday.
</P>
<P>
   The team has functioned as an expansion franchise since June
1997, working to meet NHL franchise requirements including selling
12,000 season tickets, reaching local broadcast agreements and
paying an $80 million franchise fee.
</P>
<P>
   The team now has the ability to sign eligible players and begin
to form a roster for the 2000-01 season. The Wild begin play in the
Northwest Division of the Western Conference in October.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-NY-05-01-00 2314 </TRAILER>
