<DATE_TIME> 2000-05-01 23:48 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ill. Gov. Hit in Face With Pie  </HEADLINE>
By CHRISTOPHER WILLS, Associated Press Writer
<TEXT>
<P>
   CARBONDALE, Ill. (AP) -- A protester hit Gov. George Ryan in the
face with a cream pie Monday night while he was speaking with
reporters following a public forum.
</P>
<P>
   The governor's bodyguards quickly grabbed the woman as Ryan
stepped from view.
</P>
<P>
   Ryan cleaned himself up in a nearby conference room and then
joked about the incident.
</P>
<P>
   ''It didn't taste too bad, kind of walnut or something with
cream. I don't think it was diet, though,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
   During the forum, the protester identified herself as Dawn
Roberts, a member of an organization at Southern Illinois
University at Carbondale called Students for Excellence in
Education. She asked the governor about what she said were problems
at the university.
</P>
<P>
   She and others at the forum complained that the university's
board of trustees has more Republican members than the law allows.
Ryan is a Republican.
</P>
<P>
   Critics say the board became lopsided in favor of Republicans
when the board's chairman was reappointed in January, 1999. Three
professors filed a lawsuit challenging the makeup of the board, but
it was dismissed.
</P>
<P>
   Ryan said he doubted there was anything illegal about the
board's makeup but promised to review the issue.
</P>
<P>
   After being hit with the pie, Ryan said he told his guards to
take the woman away and have her charged, and that he would sign a
complaint against her.
</P>
<P>
   Carbondale police would not say what crime she was charged with,
but said she was under arrest.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
